Fix the won't-close bug: closing the main window now reliably exits the photo-manager process. Previously the python.exe parent could stay alive idle for hours (0% CPU, no visible windows, no child processes) because Qt 6's `lastWindowClosed` signal didn't fire after the hidden main window, so `aboutToQuit` never ran and `app.exec()` parked forever. `MainWindow.closeEvent` now calls `QApplication.instance().quit()` directly when the close is accepted, bypassing the flaky last-window-closed machinery (#612).
